80%94%20%2440%20to%20%2460%20a%20month%20on%20the%20national%20median%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20then%20be%20passed%20on%20to%20the%20tenant.%20Latchel%2C%20which%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI%2C%20advertises%20that%20by%20outsourcing%20a%20landlord's%20maintenance%20costs%2C%20Latchel%20can%20generate%20savings%20of%20up%20to%20%2420%20a%20unit%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20vendors%2C%20such%20as%20CredHub%2C%20charge%20landlords%20to%20report%20rent%20payments%20to%20credit%20agencies.%20Chris%20Dukelow%2C%20CredHub's%20cofounder%2C%20said%20that%20unlike%20add-ons%20%26quot%3Bused%20more%20to%20make%20money%26quot%3B%20from%20tenants%2C%20rent%20reporting%20was%20beneficial.%20He%20said%20that%20tenants%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20opt%20out%20or%20have%20the%20cost%20folded%20into%20their%20rent%20but%20that%20most%20CredHub%20clients%20marked%20up%20the%20cost%20through%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20it's%20up%20to%20the%20property%20manager%20what%20they%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Ortscheid%20is%20a%20partner%20in%20PMAssist%2C%20a%20consulting%20company%20that%20helps%20property%20managers%20pursue%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bfee-maxing%26quot%3B%20through%20online%20courses%20that%20lay%20out%20more%20than%2075%20kinds%20of%20fees%20that%20can%20be%20charged.%20Ortscheid%20declined%20to%20comment%20but%20publicly%20credits%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20his%20own%20property%20management%20company's%20revenue%20to%20fees%20charged%20to%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrtscheid%20provides%20services%20mostly%20to%20single-family%20homes%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-orders-accidental-landlords-sell-rent-home-mortgage-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccidental%20landlords%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20inherit%20a%20rental%20property%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20from%20massive%20REITs.%20He%20credits%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Residential%20Property%20Managers%20conference%20with%20introducing%20him%20to%20%26quot%3Bfee-maxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemember%2C%20if%20a%20tenant%20will%20pay%20it%2C%20the%20market%20has%20determined%20that%20it's%20fair%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20webinar%20recording%20viewed%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2272532bfa-f41e-4965-a421-c17ec82461c7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Pushing%20the%20envelope'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%20have%20been%20slow%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20rental%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20a%20California%20judge%20ruled%20that%20Equity%20crossed%20the%20line%20with%20a%205%25%20late-payment%20fee%20that%20violated%20a%20state%20ban%20on%20marking%20up%20fees%3B%20the%20judge%20found%20that%20the%20company%20had%20charged%20more%20than%20%2436%20million%20in%20late%20fees%20in%20California%20over%20nearly%2011%20years%20and%20agreed%20with%20the%20general%20structure%20of%20the%20plaintiffs'%20calculations%20that%20found%20%2426%20million%20of%20that%20was%20excessive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20response%20to%20the%20filing%2C%20Equity%20argued%20that%20the%20calculations%20didn't%20take%20into%20account%20rising%20personnel%20costs%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20should%20limit%20monetary%20relief.%20On%20an%20April%202024%20earnings%20call%2C%20CEO%20Mark%20Parrell%20said%20the%20company%20was%20considering%20an%20appeal.%20McKenna%2C%20the%20Equity%20Residential%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20in%20the%20case%20included%20a%202008%20internal%20document%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20potential%20upside%26quot%3B%20of%20hiking%20late%20fees%20to%205%25%20of%20rent.%20Denise%20Beihoffer%2C%20the%20company's%20vice%20president%20for%20legal%20affairs%2C%20said%20Equity%20was%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20pushing%20the%20envelope%20a%20bit%20where%20the%20risk%20of%20doing%20so%20is%20low.%26quot%3B%20The%20firm's%20vice%20president%20of%20financial%20planning%20at%20the%20time%20told%20her%20in%20a%20May%202008%20email%20that%20it%20looked%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bslam%20dunk%26quot%3B%3B%20because%20California's%20average%20rent%20was%20%241%2C500%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20average%20late%20fee%20would%20come%20in%20at%20%2475%2C%26quot%3B%20a%2050%25%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20have%20been%20a%20reasonable%20calculation%3A%20The%20FTC%20has%20gone%20after%20only%20a%20few%20landlords%20over%20rental%20fees%20recently.%20And%20the%20impact%20of%20voluntary%20transparency%20efforts%20has%20been%20uneven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Biden%20White%20House's%20push%20to%20ban%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20listing%20portals%20Zillow%2C%20Apartments.com%2C%20and%20AffordableHousing.com%20agreed%20to%20display%20fees%20and%20calculate%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20renting%20for%20renters.%20But%20that%20can%20be%20only%20so%20effective.%20A%20Zillow%20spokesperson%2C%20Emily%20McDonald%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20fees%20showed%20up%20only%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20landlords%20and%20property%20managers%20provide%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226567%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joe%20Biden%20at%20an%20event%20on%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68156ac3a466d2b74ab4f541%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20called%20for%20restrictions%20on%20so-called%20junk%20fees%2C%20but%20ultimately%20did%20not%20include%20rentals%20in%20the%20new%20rule.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSusan%20Walsh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EListings%20within%20a%20property%20manager's%20control%20may%20not%20be%20complete.%20In%20the%20FTC%20case%20against%20Greystar%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20the%20company%20was%20not%20listing%20all%20fees%20on%20its%20sites.%20The%20lack%20of%20transparency%20had%20cost%20renters%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%20the%20suit%20says%2C%20citing%20one%20tenant%20whose%20actual%20monthly%20cost%20was%2040%25%20higher%20than%20what%20they%20were%20quoted%20when%20signing%20the%20lease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%2C%20Greystar%20said%20no%20tenants%20paid%20any%20fee%20%26quot%3Bthey%20have%20not%20seen%20and%20agreed%20to%20in%20their%20lease%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20had%20expressed%20willingness%2C%20in%20discussions%20with%20the%20FTC%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Bdisplay%20total%20monthly%20leasing%20price%26quot%3B%20whenever%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bwithin%20Greystar's%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreystar%20also%20said%20the%20FTC%20provided%20%26quot%3Bzero%20guidance%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20decided%20to%20exempt%20landlords%20from%20its%20rule%20on%20fee%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20effective%20path%20to%20achieving%20uniform%20and%20consistent%20fee%20disclosures%20is%20through%20clear%20regulatory%20guidelines%20for%20our%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20disappointing%20that%20the%20FTC%20has%20failed%20to%20show%20any%20leadership%20in%20this%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20via%20email%20at%20anicoll%40businessinsider.com%20and%20creyes%40businessinsider.com.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecure-news-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjunk-fees-rental-apartment-housing-costs-history-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Ins