ed%20temporary%20restraining%20orders%20partially%20blocking%20the%20orders%20from%20being%20implemented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c3a3e037-6424-4713-91fa-3eeea6d6fd21%5C%22%3E'The%20first%20thing%20we%20do%2C%20let's%20kill%20all%20the%20lawyers'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20American%20President%20has%20ever%20before%20issued%20executive%20orders%20like%20the%20one%20at%20issue%20in%20this%20lawsuit%20targeting%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-big-law-executive-orders-decisions-damage-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprominent%20law%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20adverse%20actions%20to%20be%20executed%20by%20all%20Executive%20branch%20agencies%20but%2C%20in%20purpose%20and%20effect%2C%20this%20action%20draws%20from%20a%20playbook%20as%20old%20as%20Shakespeare%2C%20who%20penned%20the%20phrase%3A%20'The%20first%20thing%20we%20do%2C%20let's%20kill%20all%20the%20lawyers%2C'%26quot%3B%20Howell%20wrote%20regarding%20the%20order%20targeting%20Perkins%20Coie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phrase%20is%20a%20reference%20to%20%26quot%3BHenry%20VI%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20three%20historical%20plays%20published%20by%20Shakespeare%20following%20the%20lifetime%20of%20King%20Henry%20VI%20of%20England.%20It%20is%20uttered%20by%20the%20villainous%20character%20Dick%20the%20Butcher%2C%20a%20henchman%20for%20the%20rebel%20leader%20Jack%20Cade%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20pair's%20strategy%20to%20seize%20power%20from%20the%20government%20of%20King%20Henry%20VI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEliminating%20lawyers%20as%20the%20guardians%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20law%20removes%20a%20major%20impediment%20to%20the%20path%20to%20more%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20Howell%20continued%20in%20her%20ruling.%20%26quot%3BIn%20a%20cringe-worthy%20twist%20on%20the%20theatrical%20phrase%20'Let's%20kill%20all%20the%20lawyers%2C'%20EO%2014230%20takes%20the%20approach%20of%20'Let's%20kill%20the%20lawyers%20I%20don't%20like%2C'%20sending%20the%20clear%20mess