nd%20sectors%2C%20women%20workers%20share%20a%20common%20reality%3A%20being%20part%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20vast%20informal%20economy.%20However%2C%20their%20roles%20come%20with%20gendered%20challenges%2C%20compounded%20by%20unsafe%20working%20conditions%2C%20lack%20of%20job%20security%2C%20exploitative%20wages%2C%20and%20systemic%20neglect.%20Women%20in%20these%20sectors%20are%20often%20disproportionately%20affected%2C%20enduring%20not%20just%20economic%20hardship%20but%20a%20lack%20of%20safety%20and%20dignity%20in%20their%20workplaces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20employment%20in%202017-2018%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20461.52%20million%20(according%20to%20the%202017-18%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey).%20The%20informal%20economy%20encompasses%20jobs%2C%20enterprises%2C%20and%20workers%20that%20exist%20outside%20state%20regulation%20or%20protection.%20These%20roles%20rarely%20offer%20fixed%20wages%2C%20job%20security%2C%20or%20benefits.%20Workers%20here%20navigate%20a%20world%20without%20contracts%2C%20safety%20nets%2C%20or%20social%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20informal%20work%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20always%20equate%20to%20poverty%2C%20it%20often%20comes%20perilously%20close.%20And%20once%20a%20family%20slips%20below%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20climbing%20back%20is%20an%20uphill%20battle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrassroots%20organisations%20are%20stepping%20in%20to%20bridge%20this%20gap%2C%20offering%20informal%20workers%20much-needed%20protection%2C%20voice%2C%20and%20measures%20to%20enable%20greater%20economic%20resilience%2C%20collective%20agency%2C%20and%20access%20to%20opportunities%20that%20can%20help%20them%20build%20more%20secure%20futures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20explores%20how%20three%20select%20grassroots%20organisations%20are%20addressing%20the%20unique%20challenges%20faced%20by%20informal%20workers%20across%20India%20and%20how%20they%20are%20driving%20transformative%20change%20from%20the%20ground%20up